WEBVTT

1
00:00:26.708 --> 00:00:28.708
["Dancing on My Own" by Robyn playing]

2
00:00:43.208 --> 00:00:44.250
[sprays]

3
00:00:52.583 --> 00:00:54.583
["Dancing on My Own" continues]

4
00:00:55.125 --> 00:00:56.333
I did it!

5
00:00:56.833 --> 00:00:58.290
Holy shit!

6
00:00:58.291 --> 00:00:59.790
It…

7
00:00:59.791 --> 00:01:01.249
Was…

8
00:01:01.250 --> 00:01:02.582
Awesome.

9
00:01:02.583 --> 00:01:03.665
Start from the top!

10
00:01:03.666 --> 00:01:06.083
I walked into school this morning.

11
00:01:08.125 --> 00:01:10.249
And then I see Colin Corwin.

12
00:01:10.250 --> 00:01:13.791
- [screams] Yeah!
<i>- ♪ Somebody said you got a new friend ♪</i>

13
00:01:18.583 --> 00:01:22.583
<i>♪ Does she love you better than I can? ♪</i>

14
00:01:25.416 --> 00:01:27.499
Jill tastes like beef jerky.

15
00:01:27.500 --> 00:01:29.624
[boys laughing]

16
00:01:29.625 --> 00:01:31.166
[girls gasp]

17
00:01:32.041 --> 00:01:34.041
[boys gasp and groan]

18
00:01:34.833 --> 00:01:38.249
I see you told everyone how you begged me to suck face.

19
00:01:38.250 --> 00:01:40.290
- Classy!
- [girls exclaim] Ooh!

20
00:01:40.291 --> 00:01:43.540
Sorry. Jill. but I'm <i>not</i> gonna be your boyfriend.

21
00:01:43.541 --> 00:01:46.499
- [boys exclaim] Oh!
- Don't flatter yourself. Colin Corwin.

22
00:01:46.500 --> 00:01:50.124
I regretted you the second
your sweaty slug lips touched mine.

23
00:01:50.125 --> 00:01:51.124
[girls exclaim]

24
00:01:51.125 --> 00:01:54.624
Hey. Jill. does your sister taste like beef jerky too.

25
00:01:54.625 --> 00:01:56.499
or just… cancer?

26
00:01:56.500 --> 00:01:57.957
- [boys and girls gasp]
- [boy] Cold.

27
00:01:57.958 --> 00:02:00.625
<i>♪ I'm just gonna dance all night… ♪</i>

28
00:02:01.583 --> 00:02:03.499
- [Jill and Colin grunt]
- Fight!

29
00:02:03.500 --> 00:02:07.832
[boy and girls chanting] Fight! Fight! Fight!

30
00:02:07.833 --> 00:02:08.874
[screams]

31
00:02:08.875 --> 00:02:10.665
[sobbing]

32
00:02:10.666 --> 00:02:13.249
You're gonna be in so much trouble.

33
00:02:13.250 --> 00:02:14.333
Mr. Corwin!

34
00:02:15.500 --> 00:02:17.749
You cry like a little bitch.

35
00:02:17.750 --> 00:02:18.999
[Colin sobs]

36
00:02:19.000 --> 00:02:21.915
He asked if I tasted like cancer?

37
00:02:21.916 --> 00:02:22.957
That's it?

38
00:02:22.958 --> 00:02:25.832
I'd rather have cancer than cystic fibrosis.

39
00:02:25.833 --> 00:02:28.707
Boys are just so embarrassing.

40
00:02:28.708 --> 00:02:30.832
Well. congratulations. You're suspended.

41
00:02:30.833 --> 00:02:31.874
Again.

42
00:02:31.875 --> 00:02:34.832
- ["Dancing on My Own" continues]
- [both laughing]

43
00:02:34.833 --> 00:02:38.458
[woman on TV] <i>Welcome to
the culinary motherland. San Francisco.</i>

44
00:02:39.333 --> 00:02:43.041
<i>♪ I just gotta see it for myself ♪</i>

45
00:02:43.541 --> 00:02:47.457
<i>♪ I'm in the corner Watching you kiss her ♪</i>

46
00:02:47.458 --> 00:02:50.291
<i>♪ Oh ♪</i>

47
00:02:51.333 --> 00:02:52.333
[Jill] Turmeric.

48
00:02:53.333 --> 00:02:55.540
Pistachio. fruit of the gods!

49
00:02:55.541 --> 00:02:58.541
<i>♪ Oh! ♪</i>

50
00:02:59.958 --> 00:03:02.040
<i>♪ I'm giving it my all... ♪</i>

51
00:03:02.041 --> 00:03:03.790
- [music stops]
- [both screaming]

52
00:03:03.791 --> 00:03:05.833
Back away. girls! Out of the way!

53
00:03:08.791 --> 00:03:10.166
[Isabelle squeaks]

54
00:03:11.041 --> 00:03:12.041
[Isabelle sighs]

55
00:03:12.750 --> 00:03:14.375
[Dad] We shoulda had boys.

56
00:03:14.958 --> 00:03:19.707
You see. the antibiotics aren't working
as well as we'd hoped.

57
00:03:19.708 --> 00:03:20.665
Hi.

58
00:03:20.666 --> 00:03:22.999
Izzy. listen. It's Robyn.

59
00:03:23.000 --> 00:03:25.540
- ["Dancing on My Own" playing]
- [gasps]

60
00:03:25.541 --> 00:03:28.165
<i>♪ On my own… ♪</i>

61
00:03:28.166 --> 00:03:29.957
- Ready?
- Ready!

62
00:03:29.958 --> 00:03:32.000
<i>♪ On my own ♪</i>

63
00:03:48.041 --> 00:03:52.707
<i>♪ So far away. but still so near… ♪</i>

64
00:03:52.708 --> 00:03:55.874
Do you really need to go out?
It's your last New Year's with us.

65
00:03:55.875 --> 00:03:57.249
I know.

66
00:03:57.250 --> 00:03:59.665
It's also my last New Year's with my friends.

67
00:03:59.666 --> 00:04:00.915
- I know.
- Bye. love you!

68
00:04:00.916 --> 00:04:01.832
- Be safe.
- Mwah! Bye!

69
00:04:01.833 --> 00:04:04.333
- [Mom] Love you.
<i>- ♪ To say goodbye ♪</i>

70
00:04:04.958 --> 00:04:06.333
You ready?

71
00:04:06.833 --> 00:04:11.040
- [woman] 15 minutes to midnight. bitches!
- [partiers whooping]

72
00:04:11.041 --> 00:04:14.165
- I'm sorry. I have gotta go. I can't…
- [moaning]

73
00:04:14.166 --> 00:04:17.832
- [moaning continues]
- [electronic dance music playing]

74
00:04:17.833 --> 00:04:20.415
[inhales. exhales]

75
00:04:20.416 --> 00:04:21.666
[sighs]

76
00:04:23.041 --> 00:04:25.582
- I'm so sorry.
- No.

77
00:04:25.583 --> 00:04:27.374
That was so fun.

78
00:04:27.375 --> 00:04:29.415
["Dancing on My Own" by Robyn playing"]

79
00:04:29.416 --> 00:04:31.999
- Sorry. Pardon me. Excuse me.
<i>- ♪ I'm giving it my all ♪</i>

80
00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:36.499
<i>♪ But I'm not the girl You're taking home… ♪</i>

81
00:04:36.500 --> 00:04:39.207
[Mom. Dad. Isabelle] Three. two. one!

82
00:04:39.208 --> 00:04:42.249
- Happy New Year!
- [whooping]

83
00:04:42.250 --> 00:04:44.666
- [Jill yelling]
- [all yelling]

84
00:04:49.208 --> 00:04:50.707
- [blows]
- [shouts]

85
00:04:50.708 --> 00:04:53.999
I have my knife skills test tomorrow.
and there's just no way for me

86
00:04:54.000 --> 00:04:57.082
to make it in time and I am so. so sorry.

87
00:04:57.083 --> 00:04:58.124
Holy sh…

88
00:04:58.125 --> 00:05:00.249
[Isabelle] <i>Don't worry. my lad.</i>

89
00:05:00.250 --> 00:05:03.707
<i>Pretty soon. you'll be headed to the culinary motherland!</i>

90
00:05:03.708 --> 00:05:05.665
<i>♪ Dancing on my own… ♪</i>

91
00:05:05.666 --> 00:05:09.624
He thought it was gonna happen in 2029. 30 years ago.

92
00:05:09.625 --> 00:05:11.999
so if we can just…

93
00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:13.207
[indistinct chatter]

94
00:05:13.208 --> 00:05:15.374
Oh. you're looking at my eye.

95
00:05:15.375 --> 00:05:18.540
- Your eye? What?
- Yeah. I look like Sloth from <i>The Goonies</i>.

96
00:05:18.541 --> 00:05:19.540
[both chuckle]

97
00:05:19.541 --> 00:05:20.999
- No. you don't.
- I know.

98
00:05:21.000 --> 00:05:23.124
- No. you don't.
- [Scott] Don't worry. It's…

99
00:05:23.125 --> 00:05:24.291
It's just pink eye.

100
00:05:25.625 --> 00:05:28.874
Well. I'm pretty sure pink eye is. like. super contagious.

101
00:05:28.875 --> 00:05:32.124
No. that's just a common misconception.

102
00:05:32.125 --> 00:05:33.915
No. really. I think it is.

103
00:05:33.916 --> 00:05:35.749
Fake news made up by Big Pharma.

104
00:05:35.750 --> 00:05:37.249
[laughs nervously]

105
00:05:37.250 --> 00:05:38.499
[Scott] Trust me.

106
00:05:38.500 --> 00:05:41.208
Your eyes. on the other hand. are super beautiful.

107
00:05:42.583 --> 00:05:44.249
[tense music playing]

108
00:05:44.250 --> 00:05:47.624
[automated voice] <i>Your call
has been forwarded to voicemail.</i>

109
00:05:47.625 --> 00:05:51.332
And then he smears butt particles all over my face.

110
00:05:51.333 --> 00:05:54.749
My face is a butthole.

111
00:05:54.750 --> 00:05:58.249
Call me tomorrow. please.

112
00:05:58.250 --> 00:05:59.375
[laughs]

113
00:06:06.041 --> 00:06:07.832
[song fades]

114
00:06:07.833 --> 00:06:09.040
[alarm chiming]

115
00:06:09.041 --> 00:06:09.957
[Jill] I'm up.

116
00:06:09.958 --> 00:06:11.958
["Almost Happy" by Laces playing]

117
00:06:18.333 --> 00:06:23.916
<i>♪ I'm just young enough To be a little numb and dumb ♪</i>

118
00:06:27.583 --> 00:06:33.208
<i>♪ Not sure how I feel But I'm sure I've seen enough ♪</i>

119
00:06:36.750 --> 00:06:40.582
<i>♪ Enough that the world Would miss me a little ♪</i>

120
00:06:40.583 --> 00:06:41.999
<i>♪ Would they say I... ♪</i>

121
00:06:42.000 --> 00:06:45.875
- [music stops]
- [coughing intensely]

122
00:06:47.791 --> 00:06:49.040
[gags]

123
00:06:49.041 --> 00:06:51.249
- [song resumes]
<i>- ♪ Here we are. here we are ♪</i>

124
00:06:51.250 --> 00:06:53.790
<i>♪ Here we are. here we are ♪</i>

125
00:06:53.791 --> 00:06:58.457
<i>♪ Hey ♪</i>

126
00:06:58.458 --> 00:07:00.749
<i>♪ Here we are. here we are ♪</i>

127
00:07:00.750 --> 00:07:04.250
<i>♪ It's like I'm almost happy ♪</i>

128
00:07:05.291 --> 00:07:09.125
<i>♪ It's like I'm almost happy ♪</i>

129
00:07:09.708 --> 00:07:10.749
[groans softly]

130
00:07:10.750 --> 00:07:11.999
[song fades]

131
00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:14.541
[dramatic classical music playing]

132
00:07:35.541 --> 00:07:37.999
[cheering]

133
00:07:38.000 --> 00:07:40.958
- [excited chatter]
- [dramatic classical music continues]

134
00:07:42.458 --> 00:07:44.458
[crowd screaming]

135
00:07:45.458 --> 00:07:46.624
<i>Bonjour!</i>

136
00:07:46.625 --> 00:07:49.249
Chef Bastien. who is your favorite chef?

137
00:07:49.250 --> 00:07:51.915
Who is my favorite chef? That is easy.

138
00:07:51.916 --> 00:07:53.582
It is <i>ma mère.</i>

139
00:07:53.583 --> 00:07:56.165
She is so beautiful. she is dead.

140
00:07:56.166 --> 00:07:59.166
Your performance on <i>Top Chef</i> changed my life.

141
00:08:01.416 --> 00:08:02.416
Ow.

142
00:08:03.791 --> 00:08:05.540
[music fades]

143
00:08:05.541 --> 00:08:08.208
[Bastien] Geoffrey! Eyes on your cake!

144
00:08:08.958 --> 00:08:10.666
- [man gasps]
- Get!

145
00:08:11.625 --> 00:08:13.458
Look at me. Don't look at me.

146
00:08:14.791 --> 00:08:15.875
Look at me.

147
00:08:16.750 --> 00:08:18.374
Never look at me!

148
00:08:18.375 --> 00:08:21.375
[tense music playing]

149
00:08:24.000 --> 00:08:26.999
Did you just look at me?
Did you just make eye contact with me?

150
00:08:27.000 --> 00:08:28.500
No. Chef.

151
00:08:34.083 --> 00:08:35.750
- [both exhale]
- [music fades]

152
00:08:36.791 --> 00:08:38.207
- Oh!
- [man grunts]

153
00:08:38.208 --> 00:08:40.624
Maybe try saying "corner" next time.

154
00:08:40.625 --> 00:08:42.166
[cooks laughing]

155
00:08:44.416 --> 00:08:45.750
[sighs]

156
00:08:51.083 --> 00:08:52.207
- You okay?
- Yeah.

157
00:08:52.208 --> 00:08:57.124
Eight hours deseeding and slicing kumquats?!

158
00:08:57.125 --> 00:08:58.290
Culinary water boarding.

159
00:08:58.291 --> 00:09:01.624
[Jill] I can't even remember
the last time I actually made anything.

160
00:09:01.625 --> 00:09:03.832
other than my brekkie burrito.

161
00:09:03.833 --> 00:09:08.874
All I do is measure. deseed. slice.
and pray for the sweet release of death.

162
00:09:08.875 --> 00:09:11.790
An AI robot could do my job better than me.

163
00:09:11.791 --> 00:09:14.124
<i>You were built for this. my dude.</i>

164
00:09:14.125 --> 00:09:15.374
Let a mofo know.

165
00:09:15.375 --> 00:09:16.749
[groans]

166
00:09:16.750 --> 00:09:19.707
I will let a mofo know I am homesick.

167
00:09:19.708 --> 00:09:22.999
I'm almost out of savings. and there's nowhere for me to go

168
00:09:23.000 --> 00:09:25.915
unless a baker quits or retires or dies.

169
00:09:25.916 --> 00:09:27.915
All right. fine. you crazy son of a bitch.

170
00:09:27.916 --> 00:09:30.540
I will fly to San Fran
and murder one of the bakers with you.

171
00:09:30.541 --> 00:09:31.915
How would we do it?

172
00:09:31.916 --> 00:09:34.915
Well. obviously. we'd wrap my oxygen cord around his neck.

173
00:09:34.916 --> 00:09:38.499
- Wow. you answered that so quickly.
- [laughing]

174
00:09:38.500 --> 00:09:41.832
Wait. speaking of lack of oxygen to the brain.

175
00:09:41.833 --> 00:09:43.999
I'm getting drinks with Equinox Ethan tomorrow.

176
00:09:44.000 --> 00:09:47.124
Isn't that the guy who thinks
that babies can breathe underwater?

177
00:09:47.125 --> 00:09:48.165
He's neurospicy.

178
00:09:48.166 --> 00:09:50.540
Have a little healthy self-love. my guy.

179
00:09:50.541 --> 00:09:51.541
Eh…

180
00:09:52.333 --> 00:09:53.999
You've gotta get on Hinge.

181
00:09:54.000 --> 00:09:55.332
<i>It's amazing.</i>

182
00:09:55.333 --> 00:09:58.415
Except for the part where you feel
like a hideous. unlovable troll

183
00:09:58.416 --> 00:10:00.041
that might match with Ted Bundy.

184
00:10:00.708 --> 00:10:03.082
- I've never been drier.
- [Jill laughs]

185
00:10:03.083 --> 00:10:06.165
I think I'd rather just live vicariously through you.

186
00:10:06.166 --> 00:10:07.166
<i>Perfect.</i>

187
00:10:10.958 --> 00:10:12.457
- Hello?
<i>- Yeah. I'm here.</i>

188
00:10:12.458 --> 00:10:13.957
- Hi.
<i>- No…</i>

189
00:10:13.958 --> 00:10:16.499
I have to tell you something. Don't freak out.

190
00:10:16.500 --> 00:10:17.582
<i>What?</i>

191
00:10:17.583 --> 00:10:20.415
[sniffles. sighs]

192
00:10:20.416 --> 00:10:21.708
Test results came back.

193
00:10:22.291 --> 00:10:25.332
- Why didn't you call me?
- I literally just did.

194
00:10:25.333 --> 00:10:28.791
<i>They're. uh… listing me for a lung transplant.</i>

195
00:10:30.250 --> 00:10:32.291
It's lookin' pretty dire. [Laughs sadly]

196
00:10:33.625 --> 00:10:35.332
They don't know what they're talking about.

197
00:10:35.333 --> 00:10:39.707
I mean. they've been wrong every single step of the way.

198
00:10:39.708 --> 00:10:41.790
You're fine. because…

199
00:10:41.791 --> 00:10:44.583
Because you're a superhero.
Have they still not figured that out yet?

200
00:10:46.041 --> 00:10:47.375
Yeah. I guess not.

201
00:10:48.625 --> 00:10:50.665
- Tsk. I'm gonna come home.
<i>- No.</i>

202
00:10:50.666 --> 00:10:52.082
- I'll look up flights now.
<i>- No.</i>

203
00:10:52.083 --> 00:10:55.374
It's not because of the results.
I miss you. I need to see you.

204
00:10:55.375 --> 00:10:57.832
You're gonna be home in three weeks for turkey.

205
00:10:57.833 --> 00:11:00.832
- For the weekend.
<i>- If you do. I will kick you in the tit.</i>

206
00:11:00.833 --> 00:11:04.124
You'll never make baker if you fly home
every time they give us shit news.

207
00:11:04.125 --> 00:11:06.124
- No. I'm...
- You are being so dramatic.

208
00:11:06.125 --> 00:11:08.445
<i>- I'm not being dramatic!</i>
- This is not <i>A Walk to Remember</i>.

209
00:11:09.416 --> 00:11:11.040
But is it <i>A Fault in Our Stars</i>?

210
00:11:11.041 --> 00:11:12.415
[chuckles]

211
00:11:12.416 --> 00:11:14.625
Shailene would def play me in my biopic.

212
00:11:15.833 --> 00:11:17.583
<i>- But no.</i>
- Okay. fine.

213
00:11:18.083 --> 00:11:20.416
But I'll see you in three weeks. Turkey!

214
00:11:23.291 --> 00:11:24.291
Jill?

215
00:11:25.250 --> 00:11:26.332
Yes. my lad?

216
00:11:26.333 --> 00:11:28.333
[poignant music playing]

217
00:11:30.500 --> 00:11:33.208
You're the most lovable person I've ever known.

218
00:11:35.708 --> 00:11:37.958
If you're a bird. I'm a bird. brother.

219
00:11:39.916 --> 00:11:41.125
<i>Call me tomorrow?</i>

220
00:11:42.333 --> 00:11:43.290
Night.

221
00:11:43.291 --> 00:11:44.291
Good night.

222
00:11:53.291 --> 00:11:54.583
[sniffles]

223
00:11:57.083 --> 00:11:59.082
[inhales. exhales]

224
00:11:59.083 --> 00:12:03.083
Jill. look. I want to be absolutely translucent.

225
00:12:03.833 --> 00:12:05.874
- "Transparent"?
- That too.

226
00:12:05.875 --> 00:12:11.040
Uh. listen. I am down to. like. hang.

227
00:12:11.041 --> 00:12:13.457
but not for anything. like. intense.

228
00:12:13.458 --> 00:12:17.082
- [inhales] Oh…
- But I am 100% committed to...

229
00:12:17.083 --> 00:12:18.540
Penetration?

230
00:12:18.541 --> 00:12:20.082
Yes!

231
00:12:20.083 --> 00:12:24.124
Oh. my God. yes. Yeah.
We are. like. on the same wavelength.

232
00:12:24.125 --> 00:12:26.874
We are just over here. finishing each other's...

233
00:12:26.875 --> 00:12:29.957
- Minds!
- [indistinct chatter]

234
00:12:29.958 --> 00:12:31.874
[cell phone buzzing]

235
00:12:31.875 --> 00:12:32.875
I'm gonna take this.

236
00:12:35.458 --> 00:12:38.166
[ominous music playing]

237
00:12:39.583 --> 00:12:42.415
[Mom on recording] <i>Jill. honey.
you need to come home right now.</i>

238
00:12:42.416 --> 00:12:43.957
<i>- Call me when you get this.</i>
- [gasps]

239
00:12:43.958 --> 00:12:47.165
[somber music playing]

240
00:12:47.166 --> 00:12:50.666
[Jill] Mom. I'm here. What's going on? How is she?

241
00:12:52.041 --> 00:12:54.874
- Talk to me. What's going on?
- [medical staff chattering indistinctly]

242
00:12:54.875 --> 00:12:57.415
- What are they saying?
- She crashed suddenly.

243
00:12:57.416 --> 00:12:58.374
Okay.

244
00:12:58.375 --> 00:13:00.125
Her oxygen levels dropped.

245
00:13:01.541 --> 00:13:03.125
She didn't make it.

246
00:13:04.166 --> 00:13:05.708
Izzy didn't make it.

