being publicly humiliated…" dream.

992
00:51:32.000 --> 00:51:33.165
- [Wes laughs]
- [chuckles]

993
00:51:33.166 --> 00:51:38.624
- That can't be the dream!
- Well. dreams are so short-sighted.

994
00:51:38.625 --> 00:51:42.332
When you're a little kid. you only know three jobs. right?

995
00:51:42.333 --> 00:51:46.415
There's. like. police officer. school teacher. and chef.

996
00:51:46.416 --> 00:51:49.249
- Mission accomplished.
- Except no.

997
00:51:49.250 --> 00:51:50.958
I'm what they call a "prep cook."

998
00:51:51.500 --> 00:51:52.915
And as Chef says.

999
00:51:52.916 --> 00:51:59.290
we are barely one step
above the janitorial staff and pedophiles.

1000
00:51:59.291 --> 00:52:02.040
Sounds like you gotta take your prep cook skills elsewhere.

1001
00:52:02.041 --> 00:52:05.165
- Mm.
- Come on. If you build it. they will come.

1002
00:52:05.166 --> 00:52:08.040
- Trust me. I'd love to start my own thing.
- What's stopping you?

1003
00:52:08.041 --> 00:52:11.165
I don't know. just any money at all. or brand reputation.

1004
00:52:11.166 --> 00:52:12.915
business plan. house specialty.

1005
00:52:12.916 --> 00:52:15.582
Oh. come on. you got a specialty.

1006
00:52:15.583 --> 00:52:17.707
Even my mom had a specialty.

1007
00:52:17.708 --> 00:52:20.707
- It was cornbread chicken pot pie.
- Oh!

1008
00:52:20.708 --> 00:52:24.415
A woman after my own heart. Do you know the recipe?

1009
00:52:24.416 --> 00:52:25.583
No. I wish.

1010
00:52:26.791 --> 00:52:28.415
It was legendary.

1011
00:52:28.416 --> 00:52:30.458
I mean. people still talk about it.

1012
00:52:32.916 --> 00:52:35.708
I wish I. uh… I wish I could remember.

1013
00:52:37.375 --> 00:52:39.250
I'll bet your taste buds do.

1014
00:52:40.166 --> 00:52:41.166
[chuckles softly]

1015
00:52:42.958 --> 00:52:46.958
All right. the suspense is killing me.
If you could put one thing on your menu.

1016
00:52:48.125 --> 00:52:49.040
what would it be?

1017
00:52:49.041 --> 00:52:53.249
You think I'm gonna share
my culinary secrets with a stranger?

1018
00:52:53.250 --> 00:52:54.499
[Wes chuckles]

1019
00:52:54.500 --> 00:52:57.040
I'll tell you what. I'm here for two weeks.

1020
00:52:57.041 --> 00:52:59.374
Why don't we try to crack this SF nut together?

1021
00:52:59.375 --> 00:53:00.957
As fellow Texas expats.

1022
00:53:00.958 --> 00:53:04.957
I feel obligated to tell you that I am girl sober.

1023
00:53:04.958 --> 00:53:06.957
so I will not make out with you.

1024
00:53:06.958 --> 00:53:09.915
Even if you beg me. I won't do it. Scout's honor.

1025
00:53:09.916 --> 00:53:13.291
["Something Like This" by CIL playing]

1026
00:53:15.750 --> 00:53:17.750
[inaudible dialogue]

1027
00:53:18.583 --> 00:53:22.749
<i>♪ Something about the day make me
Wanna put it on the line. on the wire ♪</i>

1028
00:53:22.750 --> 00:53:27.582
<i>♪ All you need to bring is yourself
Company's all that I require ♪</i>

1029
00:53:27.583 --> 00:53:31.499
<i>♪ I'm not naive for needing my baby ♪</i>

1030
00:53:31.500 --> 00:53:35.582
<i>♪ So. today. come on over And play 'cause ♪</i>

1031
00:53:35.583 --> 00:53:39.540
<i>♪ I've been patient ♪</i>

1032
00:53:39.541 --> 00:53:44.832
<i>♪ I've been waiting For something like this ♪</i>

1033
00:53:44.833 --> 00:53:46.791
<i>♪ Ooh-wee ♪</i>

1034
00:53:47.583 --> 00:53:49.040
<i>♪ Like this ♪</i>

1035
00:53:49.041 --> 00:53:53.165
<i>- ♪ Ooh-wee ♪
- ♪ Waiting for something like this ♪</i>

1036
00:53:53.166 --> 00:53:56.582
<i>- ♪ Ooh-wee ♪
- ♪ Waiting for something like ♪</i>

1037
00:53:56.583 --> 00:53:58.874
<i>♪ Baby. If you want me You know where to find me ♪</i>

1038
00:53:58.875 --> 00:54:00.957
<i>♪ I'll be ready for you. babe ♪</i>

1039
00:54:00.958 --> 00:54:04.582
<i>♪ Taste so sweet. it's like honey
Dripping down my body. babe ♪</i>

1040
00:54:04.583 --> 00:54:09.040
<i>♪ I know that this bitch love Drive you crazy ♪</i>

1041
00:54:09.041 --> 00:54:13.290
<i>♪ So. today won't you come out and play. 'cause ♪</i>

1042
00:54:13.291 --> 00:54:17.124
<i>♪ I've been patient ♪</i>

1043
00:54:17.125 --> 00:54:22.540
<i>♪ I've been waiting For something like this ♪</i>

1044
00:54:22.541 --> 00:54:25.290
<i>- ♪ Ooh-wee ♪
- ♪ Mmm ♪</i>

1045
00:54:25.291 --> 00:54:26.582
<i>♪ Like this ♪</i>

1046
00:54:26.583 --> 00:54:30.457
<i>- ♪ Ooh-wee ♪
- ♪ Waiting for something like ♪</i>

1047
00:54:30.458 --> 00:54:32.458
<i>♪ Ooh-wee ♪</i>

1048
00:54:33.625 --> 00:54:35.207
<i>♪ Like this ♪</i>

1049
00:54:35.208 --> 00:54:36.208
[song ends]

1050
00:54:40.000 --> 00:54:42.832
I don't know what happened. Chef.
I rolled it out last night.

1051
00:54:42.833 --> 00:54:44.124
and I put it in the fridge.

1052
00:54:44.125 --> 00:54:45.332
[Bastien] Apparently not.

1053
00:54:45.333 --> 00:54:47.500
- You've set us all back!
- [Jill] We could grate it.

1054
00:54:48.333 --> 00:54:49.375
[man] Whoa.

1055
00:54:50.208 --> 00:54:51.208
Or…

1056
00:54:52.708 --> 00:54:55.374
It's… I accidentally froze my butter in culinary school.

1057
00:54:55.375 --> 00:54:58.874
and grating it made the dough even flakier.

1058
00:54:58.875 --> 00:55:00.374
- You're still talking?
- [cooks laugh]

1059
00:55:00.375 --> 00:55:02.915
What is this? The Alpha Gamma prep girls?

1060
00:55:02.916 --> 00:55:04.790
[laughing]

1061
00:55:04.791 --> 00:55:07.165
- Right?
- [Arthur] Michelin-star joke. Chef.

1062
00:55:07.166 --> 00:55:09.249
[Bastien] "It makes it extra flaky."

1063
00:55:09.250 --> 00:55:11.125
[cooks laughing]

1064
00:55:17.333 --> 00:55:18.375
Hey.

1065
00:55:19.541 --> 00:55:21.208
I never asked for your help.

1066
00:55:26.458 --> 00:55:27.540
[Wes] I sold the spot.

1067
00:55:27.541 --> 00:55:28.957
- You did?
- Yeah.

1068
00:55:28.958 --> 00:55:31.124
What a star! We have to celebrate.

1069
00:55:31.125 --> 00:55:33.665
- After you. How was your day?
- [Jill chuckles]

1070
00:55:33.666 --> 00:55:35.707
- Uh…
- [passengers chattering]

1071
00:55:35.708 --> 00:55:39.665
[clears throat] Chef Bastien was feeling particularly evil.

1072
00:55:39.666 --> 00:55:41.165
He didn't use a single 'quat.

1073
00:55:41.166 --> 00:55:43.957
He literally poured them out into the trash can

1074
00:55:43.958 --> 00:55:46.125
while maintaining eye contact with me.

1075
00:55:46.708 --> 00:55:49.832
It was kumquat carnage.

1076
00:55:49.833 --> 00:55:51.082
He's hazing you. Jill.

1077
00:55:51.083 --> 00:55:52.083
[sighs]

1078
00:55:53.958 --> 00:55:55.625
I don't know if I'm built for this.

1079
00:55:56.208 --> 00:55:57.457
What. this Flâner gig?

1080
00:55:57.458 --> 00:55:58.458
This…

1081
00:55:59.666 --> 00:56:00.875
This dream.

1082
00:56:02.625 --> 00:56:06.915
Ignore me and my existential dread.

1083
00:56:06.916 --> 00:56:07.916
[chuckles]

1084
00:56:08.458 --> 00:56:12.541
It's your last day. and I am ready to giggle.

1085
00:56:14.291 --> 00:56:16.040
Welcome to Golden Gate Giggles.

1086
00:56:16.041 --> 00:56:16.957
[whoops]

1087
00:56:16.958 --> 00:56:18.249
I'm your tour guide. Walter.

1088
00:56:18.250 --> 00:56:23.082
and we're so glad you chose us. Golden Gate Giggles.

1089
00:56:23.083 --> 00:56:24.957
How about a joke?

1090
00:56:24.958 --> 00:56:26.041
Sure.

1091
00:56:26.875 --> 00:56:28.291
Why did the hipster refuse…

1092
00:56:31.958 --> 00:56:34.791
"Why did the hipster refuse
to cross the Golden Gate Bridge?"

1093
00:56:35.500 --> 00:56:36.582
[both] Why?

1094
00:56:36.583 --> 00:56:38.749
Because it was too mainstream.

1095
00:56:38.750 --> 00:56:40.082
Pause for laughs.

1096
00:56:40.083 --> 00:56:41.541
[laughs]

1097
00:56:42.125 --> 00:56:45.457
- It's my first day today.
- [microphone feedback squeals]

1098
00:56:45.458 --> 00:56:49.166
- Crushing it. Walter.
- Let's start out with some funny facts.

1099
00:56:49.916 --> 00:56:50.958
Sure.

1100
00:56:51.750 --> 00:56:52.790
Ha!

1101
00:56:52.791 --> 00:56:57.040
San Francisco is where they invented blue jeans.

1102
00:56:57.041 --> 00:56:58.208
and the electric…

1103
00:56:58.833 --> 00:57:00.457
- I can't do this.
- You're doing fine.

1104
00:57:00.458 --> 00:57:02.165
- Just take a deep breath.
- I quit.

1105
00:57:02.166 --> 00:57:04.665
- [driver] You can't. We got 2 hours left.
- [Walter] Let me off!

1106
00:57:04.666 --> 00:57:07.374
- Nope. Sit down and take a breath.
- Open the door! [Yells]

1107
00:57:07.375 --> 00:57:09.207
- [driver] I need this job!
- Open the door!

1108
00:57:09.208 --> 00:57:11.832
- Let me off!
- This is why I don't have kids.

1109
00:57:11.833 --> 00:57:13.499
Let me off!

1110
00:57:13.500 --> 00:57:15.541
[panting]

1111
00:57:21.833 --> 00:57:24.874
Hey. boss. We paid for giggles.

1112
00:57:24.875 --> 00:57:27.999
- Not my department.
- [passengers groaning]

1113
00:57:28.000 --> 00:57:29.582
[woman] We gonna get a refund?

1114
00:57:29.583 --> 00:57:32.000
[passengers chattering indistinctly]

1115
00:57:34.791 --> 00:57:35.916
What are you doing?

1116
00:57:36.416 --> 00:57:37.416
[Wes] Uh…

1117
00:57:38.833 --> 00:57:40.083
Uh. what's up. guys?

1118
00:57:40.833 --> 00:57:42.124
I'm Wes.

1119
00:57:42.125 --> 00:57:43.999
So. where's everybody from?

1120
00:57:44.000 --> 00:57:46.707
- Uh. other than New Jersey.
- [passengers chuckle]

1121
00:57:46.708 --> 00:57:48.540
Look. kid. you gotta sit down. Now.

1122
00:57:48.541 --> 00:57:51.082
Uh. I know. I'm sorry. I just… We came for giggles. right?

1123
00:57:51.083 --> 00:57:53.415
- Yeah.
- [Wes] Let's get some giggles in here.

1124
00:57:53.416 --> 00:57:58.916
Uh. up ahead. we've got the world-famous…

1125
00:57:59.541 --> 00:58:00.915
Squiggle street.

1126
00:58:00.916 --> 00:58:04.457
["San Francisco Blues" by Peggy Lee playing]

1127
00:58:04.458 --> 00:58:07.582
On your right. we have. uh. the house

1128
00:58:07.583 --> 00:58:12.374
where Robin Williams brought a donkey
into the party in <i>Mrs. Doubtfire</i>.

1129
00:58:12.375 --> 00:58:13.957
[passengers exclaiming]

1130
00:58:13.958 --> 00:58:16.749
<i>♪ Go to Fisherman's Wharf ♪</i>

1131
00:58:16.750 --> 00:58:18.583
<i>♪ Top of the Mark ♪</i>

1132
00:58:19.166 --> 00:58:20.624
<i>♪ Telegraph Hill ♪</i>

1133
00:58:20.625 --> 00:58:22.290
<i>♪ Golden Gate Park ♪</i>

1134
00:58:22.291 --> 00:58:27.082
<i>♪ Baby. baby. baby There's so much in this town… ♪</i>

1135
00:58:27.083 --> 00:58:30.249
[Wes] Out in the bay. you see it? That is Alcatraz.

1136
00:58:30.250 --> 00:58:34.165
the famous prison that is known
for hosting legendary criminals

1137
00:58:34.166 --> 00:58:37.749
like Al Capone and. um. Sean Connery.

1138
00:58:37.750 --> 00:58:38.665
[passengers laugh]

1139
00:58:38.666 --> 00:58:42.207
Okay. look. child. you're gonna have
to sit down now or I will kick you off.

1140
00:58:42.208 --> 00:58:44.082
- Last thing. On your left…
- [driver] Seriously?

1141
00:58:44.083 --> 00:58:47.457
…Is the delectable Flâner. I don't want to embarrass her.

1142
00:58:47.458 --> 00:58:49.374
but we are actually in the presence

1143
00:58:49.375 --> 00:58:53.165
of one of San Francisco's
most talented up-and-coming chefs.

1144
00:58:53.166 --> 00:58:57.541
She taught Chef Bastien everything he knows because she...

1145
00:58:58.041 --> 00:59:02.916
she is most definitely built for this.

1146
00:59:03.666 --> 00:59:06.040
- [driver] Okay. Romeo. show's over.
- [passengers groan]

1147
00:59:06.041 --> 00:59:08.915
- I'm going. I just have one more thing.
- I know you are. No. you don't.

1148
00:59:08.916 --> 00:59:12.415
- Let's go. And you're done.
<i>- ♪ I left my heart ♪</i>

1149
00:59:12.416 --> 00:59:15.415
- Off! Uh-huh. All right.
<i>- ♪ In San Francisco ♪</i>

1150
00:59:15.416 --> 00:59:16.499
I just need to finish!

1151
00:59:16.500 --> 00:59:18.624
- [man 1] <i>♪ High on a hill ♪
- </i> Dude!

1152
00:59:18.625 --> 00:59:22.374
[all] <i>♪ She calls to me ♪</i>

1153
00:59:22.375 --> 00:59:25.832
- Let go!
<i>- ♪ When I come home to you ♪</i>

1154
00:59:25.833 --> 00:59:30.082
- [driver] All right. Fine.
<i>- ♪ San Francisco! ♪</i>

1155
00:59:30.083 --> 00:59:34.124
<i>♪ Your golden sun ♪</i>

1156
00:59:34.125 --> 00:59:36.665
<i>♪ Will shine ♪</i>

1157
00:59:36.666 --> 00:59:40.957
<i>♪ For me ♪</i>

1158
00:59:40.958 --> 00:59:43.040
[passengers cheering]

1159
00:59:43.041 --> 00:59:45.041
[hopeful music playing]

1160
00:59:50.083 --> 00:59:52.083
[music turns dramatic]

1161
01:00:03.708 --> 01:00:06.665
I guess the scouts have no honor. huh?

1162
01:00:06.666 --> 01:00:08.540
It's a good thing I wasn't a Boy Scout.

1163
01:00:08.541 --> 01:00:10.790
- [man 1 whistles]
- [passengers cheering]

1164
01:00:10.791 --> 01:00:12.374
[man 2] Yeah. all right!

1165
01:00:12.375 --> 01:00:14.333
[passengers cheering and whooping]

1166
01:00:14.916 --> 01:00:16.290
Ah. ta-da!

1167
01:00:16.291 --> 01:00:19.415
Blue crab and corn fritters with smoked jalapeño aioli.

1168
01:00:19.416 --> 01:00:21.249
- Wow.
- Voilà!

1169
01:00:21.250 --> 01:00:23.041
- [Wes] This is insane.
- Yay.

1170
01:00:23.625 --> 01:00:24.625
[Wes chuckles]

1171
01:00:26.958 --> 01:00:28.332
- What?
- Is it good?

1172
01:00:28.333 --> 01:00:30.832
Are you kidding me? Chef Bastien is an idiot.

1173
01:00:30.833 --> 01:00:32.374
He is sitting on a gold mine.

1174
01:00:32.375 --> 01:00:34.125
How did you even learn how to do this?

1175
01:00:35.666 --> 01:00:37.082
Um…

1176
01:00:37.083 --> 01:00:40.707
["Either Way I Lose" by Meshell
Ndegeocello playing over speakers]

1177
01:00:40.708 --> 01:00:42.791
My sister was stuck at home a lot as a kid.

1178
01:00:44.791 --> 01:00:46.707
She was really sick.

1179
01:00:46.708 --> 01:00:50.541
And the kitchen was our happy place.

1180
01:00:51.041 --> 01:00:53.290
We were like two little mad scientists.

1181
01:00:53.291 --> 01:00:54.874
- [laughs]
- [chuckles]

1182
01:00:54.875 --> 01:00:57.874
We always thought we were
on the verge of discovering something

1183
01:00:57.875 --> 01:00:59.582
the world had never seen.

1184
01:00:59.583 --> 01:01:00.583
- [laughs]
- [chuckles]

1185
01:01:02.916 --> 01:01:05.625
<i>♪ Either way I lose ♪</i>

1186
01:01:09.750 --> 01:01:11.750
<i>♪ Though I know… ♪</i>

1187
01:01:13.458 --> 01:01:14.625
My sister…

1188
01:01:15.583 --> 01:01:16.916
Isabelle. she died.

1189
01:01:17.791 --> 01:01:20.875
In November. She had cystic fibrosis.

1190
01:01:22.458 --> 01:01:23.749
I'm so sorry. Jill.

1191
01:01:23.750 --> 01:01:26.125
She was just the love of my life. No big.

1192
01:01:27.541 --> 01:01:29.875
- I bet she's proud of you.
- Uh…

1193
01:01:32.125 --> 01:01:36.249
I was much cooler as a kid. I peaked at like 12.

1194
01:01:36.250 --> 01:01:37.333
[both chuckle]

1195
01:01:37.916 --> 01:01:41.749
I would do the craziest shit
just to come home with a story for her.

1196
01:01:41.750 --> 01:01:43.510
I would've tried crack if it made her laugh.

1197
01:01:44.041 --> 01:01:48.249
And now. I think I might be a little bit dead inside.

1198
01:01:48.250 --> 01:01:49.250
Jill…

1199
01:01:52.833 --> 01:01:54.958
You couldn't be less dead inside.

1200
01:01:56.666 --> 01:01:57.915
What you need to do

1201
01:01:57.916 --> 01:01:59.708
is you need to get out there

1202
01:02:00.291 --> 01:02:01.290
and try crack.

1203
01:02:01.291 --> 01:02:03.416
[laughs]

1204
01:02:04.291 --> 01:02:05.291
Come with me…

1205
01:02:07.166 --> 01:02:08.708
To Breeda and Andy's wedding.

1206
01:02:10.000 --> 01:02:11.000
Hm.

1207
01:02:12.541 --> 01:02:14.208
Okay. [Laughs nervously]

1208
01:02:14.833 --> 01:02:16.666
- I'll ask my overlord.
- [snickers]

1209
01:02:19.416 --> 01:02:20.416
All right.

1210
01:02:21.791 --> 01:02:23.082
Ready for the main course?

1211
01:02:23.083 --> 01:02:24.166
There's more?

1212
01:02:25.541 --> 01:02:28.415
- I… This was already so impressive.
- Come on!

1213
01:02:28.416 --> 01:02:30.374
- How could you make more? I don't even…
- [laughs]

1214
01:02:30.375 --> 01:02:31.875
- Shut up.
- You can't top this.

1215
01:02:35.083 --> 01:02:36.083
Okay.

1216
01:02:39.625 --> 01:02:42.833
<i>♪ Either way I lose… ♪</i>

1217
01:02:44.291 --> 01:02:45.915
Is that chicken pot pie?

1218
01:02:45.916 --> 01:02:47.708
With cornbread crust.

1219
01:02:49.750 --> 01:02:51.082
You made this for me?

1220
01:02:51.083 --> 01:02:53.832
Yeah. I mean. I have no idea
if it's anything like your mom's.

1221
01:02:53.833 --> 01:02:56.916
It was a full-blown experiment. but we will see.

1222
01:02:57.583 --> 01:02:58.583
All right.

1223
01:02:59.583 --> 01:03:02.583
[wistful music playing]

1224
01:03:25.291 --> 01:03:26.583
Uh…

1225
01:03:28.250 --> 01:03:32.291
I'm gonna go… Just… I'm gonna prep dessert. okay?

1226
01:03:51.125 --> 01:03:53.125
["Cherish You" by Mikky Ekko playing]

1227
01:03:58.541 --> 01:04:00.874
<i>♪ Believe it ♪</i>

1228
01:04:00.875 --> 01:04:05.041
<i>♪ I need you by my side ♪</i>

1229
01:04:05.541 --> 01:04:07.957
<i>♪ Yes. I know you know ♪</i>

1230
01:04:07.958 --> 01:04:12.332
<i>♪ Know you know Know I've been a sinner. baby ♪</i>

1231
01:04:12.333 --> 01:04:14.707
<i>♪ I've seen it ♪</i>

1232
01:04:14.708 --> 01:04:18.791
<i>♪ I've seen you high and dry ♪</i>

1233
01:04:19.708 --> 01:04:21.874
<i>♪ Yes. I know you don't ♪</i>

1234
01:04:21.875 --> 01:04:27.832
<i>♪ Know you don't Know you don't need me to say it ♪</i>

1235
01:04:27.833 --> 01:04:31.040
<i>♪ But if anything happens between us
Does everything change? ♪</i>

1236
01:04:31.041 --> 01:04:32.332
[pots and pans clanking]

1237
01:04:32.333 --> 01:04:37.290
<i>♪ I know you feel it too I can see it in your face ♪</i>

1238
01:04:37.291 --> 01:04:41.458
<i>♪ So tell me now not to get too close ♪</i>

1239
01:04:42.750 --> 01:04:44.040
<i>♪ 'Cause it always happens ♪</i>

1240
01:04:44.041 --> 01:04:46.624
<i>♪ One. two. three. four ♪</i>

1241
01:04:46.625 --> 01:04:49.374
<i>♪ How much longer can this go? ♪</i>

1242
01:04:49.375 --> 01:04:51.207
<i>♪ Oh. babe. don't break ♪</i>

1243
01:04:51.208 --> 01:04:53.874
<i>♪ Every single breath you take ♪</i>

1244
01:04:53.875 --> 01:04:58.040
<i>♪ Kills me softly. chills my body ♪</i>

1245
01:04:58.041 --> 01:04:59.915
<i>♪ But when we reach the limit ♪</i>

1246
01:04:59.916 --> 01:05:01.457
- [song ends]
- [dishes clattering]

1247
01:05:01.458 --> 01:05:02.499
- Sorry.
- No. Sorry.

1248
01:05:02.500 --> 01:05:04.415
- Yeah… I just have to go to the bathroom.
- Okay.

1249
01:05:04.416 --> 01:05:05.332
[thuds]

1250
01:05:05.333 --> 01:05:06.332
All right. You okay?

1251
01:05:06.333 --> 01:05:07.249
- Yep.
- Okay.

1252
01:05:07.250 --> 01:05:08.708
- [Wes] Sorry. Uh…
- Oh. no. Okay.

1253
01:05:10.750 --> 01:05:11.750
Okay.

1254
01:05:12.291 --> 01:05:13.915
[inhales. exhales]

1255
01:05:13.916 --> 01:05:15.915
Just say it. Just say the words.

1256
01:05:15.916 --> 01:05:17.374
Just say it.

1257
01:05:17.375 --> 01:05:19.541
Jill. Hey. Jill. I've been…

1258
01:05:20.416 --> 01:05:23.000
I've been getting your voice mails. I've been getting…

1259
01:05:25.208 --> 01:05:27.750
Oh. shit.

1260
01:05:29.291 --> 01:05:30.666
[exhales sharply]

1261
01:05:31.291 --> 01:05:32.624
[sighs]

1262
01:05:32.625 --> 01:05:33.625
[sniffs]

1263
01:05:34.416 --> 01:05:36.708
[inhales. exhales]

1264
01:05:44.500 --> 01:05:45.750
[door opens]

1265
01:05:46.333 --> 01:05:47.333
Jill.

1266
01:05:48.750 --> 01:05:49.791
Uh…

1267
01:05:52.916 --> 01:05:54.125
I. um…

1268
01:05:55.458 --> 01:05:56.541
[sucks through teeth]

1269
01:05:58.958 --> 01:06:00.000
No. it's okay.

1270
01:06:01.041 --> 01:06:02.250
It's totally okay.

1271
01:06:03.500 --> 01:06:04.500
Um…

1272
01:06:06.333 --> 01:06:08.041
Want to just watch <i>Top Chef</i>?

1273
01:06:08.833 --> 01:06:12.790
[woman on TV] <i>I took a date-based ganache.
I shaped it into a small sphere.</i>

1274
01:06:12.791 --> 01:06:15.915
<i>and I coated it in a cocoa-infused beignet dough before…</i>

1275
01:06:15.916 --> 01:06:18.083
Jill. I've been getting your voice mails.

1276
01:06:18.625 --> 01:06:20.957
[man 1 on TV] <i>I like the surprise in the middle. It's nice.</i>

1277
01:06:20.958 --> 01:06:23.582
[man 2] <i>I went with a bombolone-style donut.</i>

1278
01:06:23.583 --> 01:06:26.749
<i>I worked in fresh orange and lemon zest. fried it off.</i>

1279
01:06:26.750 --> 01:06:29.582
<i>and finished it with a passion fruit cream filling.</i>

1280
01:06:29.583 --> 01:06:31.249
- [man 1] <i>The texture's great.</i>
- [Wes sighs]

1281
01:06:31.250 --> 01:06:32.832
<i>♪ Heaven help me ♪</i>

1282
01:06:32.833 --> 01:06:38.082
<i>♪ My mind changes like the wind ♪</i>

1283
01:06:38.083 --> 01:06:40.040
["Waking Up Slow" by Gabrielle Aplin playing]

1284
01:06:40.041 --> 01:06:42.332
<i>♪ Please excuse me ♪</i>

1285
01:06:42.333 --> 01:06:47.832
<i>♪ I don't know where to begin ♪</i>

1286
01:06:47.833 --> 01:06:51.749
<i>♪ But I didn't think I cared ♪</i>

1287
01:06:51.750 --> 01:06:54.124
<i>♪ I could be your friend ♪</i>

1288
01:06:54.125 --> 01:06:58.832
<i>♪ But I'm unprepared Oh. I've never felt like this ♪</i>

1289
01:06:58.833 --> 01:07:01.124
<i>♪ I was unaware ♪</i>

1290
01:07:01.125 --> 01:07:03.582
<i>♪ That you were lighting flares ♪</i>

1291
01:07:03.583 --> 01:07:08.457
<i>♪ Now I'm running scared Oh. how did it come to this? ♪</i>

1292
01:07:08.458 --> 01:07:15.458
<i>♪ You know I've never Been so lonely on my own ♪</i>

1293
01:07:16.041 --> 01:07:17.999
<i>♪ And it shows ♪</i>

1294
01:07:18.000 --> 01:07:22.791
<i>♪ 'Cause I don't see you like I used to ♪</i>

1295
01:07:23.958 --> 01:07:26.582
<i>♪ Now I'm going back On the things that I know ♪</i>

1296
01:07:26.583 --> 01:07:32.832
<i>♪ Oh. all my nights taste like gold ♪</i>

1297
01:07:32.833 --> 01:07:37.082
<i>♪ Yeah. when I'm with you It's like everything glows ♪</i>

1298
01:07:37.083 --> 01:07:42.165
<i>♪ And all my days. we can lay low ♪</i>

1299
01:07:42.166 --> 01:07:46.707
<i>♪ Yeah. when we're waking up We're waking up slow ♪</i>

1300
01:07:46.708 --> 01:07:48.000
[song fades]

1301
01:07:51.083 --> 01:07:52.791
Dessert tacos.

1302
01:07:53.625 --> 01:07:54.875
Dessert tacos?

1303
01:07:55.375 --> 01:07:58.249
When Izzy was super sick. they tried to get her to eat.

1304
01:07:58.250 --> 01:08:00.666
and she'd throw everything up except her favorite.

1305
01:08:01.583 --> 01:08:06.500
Dessert tacos. And <i>that</i> is my specialty.

1306
01:08:12.666 --> 01:08:13.958
<i>Magic: The Gathering.</i>

1307
01:08:14.666 --> 01:08:15.833
The card game?

1308
01:08:17.666 --> 01:08:20.207
Actually. they're not just cards.
They're actually collectible.

1309
01:08:20.208 --> 01:08:21.665
They're really valuable.

1310
01:08:21.666 --> 01:08:24.250
But. um. my mom. uh…

1311
01:08:24.916 --> 01:08:26.957
She would buy them for me.

1312
01:08:26.958 --> 01:08:29.708
and she bought me my first pack. and…

1313
01:08:30.791 --> 01:08:34.665
I just need the Alpha Black Lotus
to complete the Power Nine.

1314
01:08:34.666 --> 01:08:37.290
It's one of the rarest cards in the world.

1315
01:08:37.291 --> 01:08:40.082
That's what I've been… working towards.

1316
01:08:40.083 --> 01:08:41.082
Wow.

1317
01:08:41.083 --> 01:08:44.582
And I think I may have found one on eBay.

1318
01:08:44.583 --> 01:08:45.915
- Really?
- Yeah.

1319
01:08:45.916 --> 01:08:46.916
So…

1320
01:08:47.500 --> 01:08:50.957
I gotta confess. I was actually gonna ghost you

1321
01:08:50.958 --> 01:08:54.332
for not having the full… Power Nine.

1322
01:08:54.333 --> 01:08:55.790
- [chuckles]
- So now I don't have to.

1323
01:08:55.791 --> 01:08:57.290
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

1324
01:08:57.291 --> 01:08:59.791
Okay. wow. Still in the game.

1325
01:09:01.000 --> 01:09:02.250
Still in the game.

1326
01:09:03.875 --> 01:09:05.082
I'll see you at home.

1327
01:09:05.083 --> 01:09:06.083
Yeah.

1328
01:09:06.500 --> 01:09:07.541
Safe flight.

1329
01:09:08.458 --> 01:09:09.458
Thanks.

1330
01:09:28.750 --> 01:09:30.374
[Andy and Breeda laughing]

1331
01:09:30.375 --> 01:09:32.749
[Wes] Last breath of freedom till you're chained for life.

1332
01:09:32.750 --> 01:09:34.666
- Hey!
- Yay!

1333
01:09:35.416 --> 01:09:36.582
[cell phone ringing]

1334
01:09:36.583 --> 01:09:38.624
Oh! We are excited to meet Jill.

1335
01:09:38.625 --> 01:09:40.265
- [Breeda] Yeah. we are.
- [ringing stops]

1336
01:09:41.750 --> 01:09:43.165
- Oh. no.
- [groans]

1337
01:09:43.166 --> 01:09:44.165
I knew it.

1338
01:09:44.166 --> 01:09:45.332
What happened. Wes?

1339
01:09:45.333 --> 01:09:47.083
Nothing. Nothing.

1340
01:09:47.791 --> 01:09:49.874
- We're just hanging out.
- [both groan]

1341
01:09:49.875 --> 01:09:54.415
All right. I admit that things
have gotten a little intense.

1342
01:09:54.416 --> 01:09:58.540
Intense? You're the one
that flew to another city for this girl.

1343
01:09:58.541 --> 01:10:00.790
No. I flew to another city for work.

1344
01:10:00.791 --> 01:10:03.124
- Oh. for work.
- Oh. yes. of course.

1345
01:10:03.125 --> 01:10:04.665
- It was a work trip.
- Work trip. and...

1346
01:10:04.666 --> 01:10:07.165
All I'm saying is once in a while. Wes.

1347
01:10:07.166 --> 01:10:10.665
someone comes along that changes the whole game.

1348
01:10:10.666 --> 01:10:13.916
Yeah. don't be so busy scoring that you miss it.

1349
01:10:15.083 --> 01:10:16.874
- [scoffs]
- Wow.

1350
01:10:16.875 --> 01:10:19.332
- That was good. So good.
- That was nice.

1351
01:10:19.333 --> 01:10:21.582
- [Breeda] Copyright that.
- [Andy] Every single time.

1352
01:10:21.583 --> 01:10:25.458
Wait a minute. Wait. You didn't tell us
what happened with the voice mails.

1353
01:10:26.041 --> 01:10:27.333
[groans]

1354
01:10:27.875 --> 01:10:29.749
- You didn't tell her?
- O.M. God.

1355
01:10:29.750 --> 01:10:30.665
I'm going to.

1356
01:10:30.666 --> 01:10:32.040
- Liar. liar!
- Guys. look.

1357
01:10:32.041 --> 01:10:35.540
Oh. my God. this is like a sick reboot of <i>You've Got Mail</i>.

1358
01:10:35.541 --> 01:10:37.457
Tom Hanks is America's sweetheart!

1359
01:10:37.458 --> 01:10:39.541
[in unison] You are not Tom Hanks!

1360
01:10:40.041 --> 01:10:41.249
I might slap him.

1361
01:10:41.250 --> 01:10:42.915
- Violence is never...
- [Breeda] Slap him.

1362
01:10:42.916 --> 01:10:45.582
- [Wes] Hey! Hey!
- Wes. tell her the truth.

1363
01:10:45.583 --> 01:10:47.540
- I'm going to.
- Okay? Yes.

1364
01:10:47.541 --> 01:10:51.540
- [in unison] Tell her the truth. Wes.
- I will! In person.

1365
01:10:51.541 --> 01:10:52.958
I swear on my mom.

1366
01:10:53.458 --> 01:10:55.790
- [exhales]
- [indistinct chatter]

1367
01:10:55.791 --> 01:10:56.707
[Wes sighs]

1368
01:10:56.708 --> 01:10:59.082
- Well. now we can't say anything.
- Yeah.

1369
01:10:59.083 --> 01:11:01.500
[playing alluring melody]

1370
01:11:03.875 --> 01:11:06.208
[exhales. sniffs]

1371
01:11:08.875 --> 01:11:11.916
["Beige" by York Lore playing]

1372
01:11:18.000 --> 01:11:21.207
<i>♪ I don't wanna see you smile ♪</i>

1373
01:11:21.208 --> 01:11:24.124
<i>♪ I want you in the morning ♪</i>

1374
01:11:24.125 --> 01:11:27.375
<i>♪ Before you go performing ♪</i>

1375
01:11:29.500 --> 01:11:32.874
<i>♪ Tell me something I don't know ♪</i>

1376
01:11:32.875 --> 01:11:38.583
<i>♪ And lead me to the place Where no one ever goes ♪</i>

1377
01:11:40.791 --> 01:11:43.790
<i>♪ You know you're beautiful ♪</i>

1378
01:11:43.791 --> 01:11:46.457
<i>♪ But that ain't half the gold treasure In your soul ♪</i>

1379
01:11:46.458 --> 01:11:49.374
<i>♪ What you got? 'Cause I want it all ♪</i>

1380
01:11:49.375 --> 01:11:51.957
<i>♪ With your fingers in my mouth I fail to see your faults ♪</i>

1381
01:11:51.958 --> 01:11:59.665
<i>♪ So please don't let me fall ♪</i>

1382
01:11:59.666 --> 01:12:11.665
<i>♪ Don't let me fall ♪</i>

1383
01:12:11.666 --> 01:12:13.290
- [song fades]
- [glass clinking]

1384
01:12:13.291 --> 01:12:15.374
Good evening. everyone. I'm Wes.

1385
01:12:15.375 --> 01:12:17.790
[cheering and whooping]

1386
01:12:17.791 --> 01:12:18.957
[whoops]

1387
01:12:18.958 --> 01:12:21.665
Andy's younger. dreamier cousin.

1388
01:12:21.666 --> 01:12:23.207
- Lies.
- [Wes] If not by blood.

1389
01:12:23.208 --> 01:12:24.875
Our mothers were best friends.

1390
01:12:25.708 --> 01:12:28.790
And Breeda is the older sister that I never had.

1391
01:12:28.791 --> 01:12:30.040
[guests] Aww.

1392
01:12:30.041 --> 01:12:35.124
So I tried to warn 'em both
that marriage is Russian roulette. okay?

1393
01:12:35.125 --> 01:12:38.041
- Should we go over the divorce rate?
- [all] No.

1394
01:12:38.791 --> 01:12:43.749
Okay. suffice it to say.
I wouldn't consider myself a romantic.

1395
01:12:43.750 --> 01:12:44.791
[woman] Aw.

1396
01:12:46.416 --> 01:12:49.416
[poignant music playing]

1397
01:12:50.333 --> 01:12:51.708
But. um…

1398
01:12:53.208 --> 01:12:57.874
Did you know that these two weren't even supposed to meet?

1399
01:12:57.875 --> 01:13:00.207
Andy's alarm randomly didn't go off.

1400
01:13:00.208 --> 01:13:04.165
This man has never been late
to anything in his entire life.

1401
01:13:04.166 --> 01:13:07.499
And he missed his dentist appointment.
And he loves the dentist.

1402
01:13:07.500 --> 01:13:09.165
[guests laughing]

1403
01:13:09.166 --> 01:13:10.082
- It's true.
- I do.

1404
01:13:10.083 --> 01:13:13.833
They made him wait for an hour.
and he was about to walk out.

1405
01:13:14.583 --> 01:13:15.957
when Breeda walked in.

1406
01:13:15.958 --> 01:13:17.165
[man] Aww.

1407
01:13:17.166 --> 01:13:19.833
[Wes] If that alarm had gone off when it was supposed to.

1408
01:13:20.791 --> 01:13:24.124
these two would never have met.
and we would not be here tonight.

1409
01:13:24.125 --> 01:13:26.165
[guests chattering softly]

1410
01:13:26.166 --> 01:13:28.541
I don't know about gambling on forever.

1411
01:13:30.208 --> 01:13:31.583
but I do know this.

1412
01:13:32.083 --> 01:13:33.791
You're proof

1413
01:13:34.583 --> 01:13:36.250
that sometimes

1414
01:13:37.916 --> 01:13:39.957
life rigs things in our favor.

1415
01:13:39.958 --> 01:13:41.958
[poignant music intensifies]

1416
01:13:47.666 --> 01:13:48.790
To Breeda and Andy.

1417
01:13:48.791 --> 01:13:50.416
Yeah!

1418
01:13:53.041 --> 01:13:54.499
You made a believer out of me.

1419
01:13:54.500 --> 01:13:56.125
[guests cheering and whistling]

1420
01:13:59.166 --> 01:14:02.999
- I am so proud of you.
- Couldn't have done it without you. coach.

1421
01:14:03.000 --> 01:14:04.290
[Jill] That was beautiful.

1422
01:14:04.291 --> 01:14:06.457
- Your hands are so cold.
- I know. [Laughs]

1423
01:14:06.458 --> 01:14:08.665
- What?
- [guests chattering]

1424
01:14:08.666 --> 01:14:10.124
Wait. let's warm you up.

1425
01:14:10.125 --> 01:14:11.165
Jeez.

1426
01:14:11.166 --> 01:14:13.999
["Ride the Storm" by Goldford playing over speakers]

1427
01:14:14.000 --> 01:14:15.000
Thanks.

1428
01:14:15.458 --> 01:14:17.583
- Can I top you off?
- Yes. please.

1429
01:14:19.166 --> 01:14:20.166
Thanks.

1430
01:14:21.958 --> 01:14:23.665
- [Andy] There she is.
- Oh. my God! Jill!

1431
01:14:23.666 --> 01:14:25.540
Oh. wow. I am so starstruck.

1432
01:14:25.541 --> 01:14:27.207
- Oh. my God!
- [all laugh]

1433
01:14:27.208 --> 01:14:29.915
<i>♪ We can ride the storm… ♪</i>

1434
01:14:29.916 --> 01:14:32.707
Can I get one more and a whiskey on the rocks?

1435
01:14:32.708 --> 01:14:35.165
- Yes.
- Thank you for being here. You're so cute.

1436
01:14:35.166 --> 01:14:37.416
- Congrats!
- Enjoy. Thank you!

1437
01:14:39.041 --> 01:14:41.457
- [Breeda] Oh. my God.
- [Andy] Look who decided to show up!

1438
01:14:41.458 --> 01:14:42.499
[line dialing]

1439
01:14:42.500 --> 01:14:44.625
[cell phone buzzing]

1440
01:14:45.625 --> 01:14:46.874
[dialing and buzzing continue]

1441
01:14:46.875 --> 01:14:52.375
<i>♪ We can make it through it all ♪</i>

1442
01:14:53.541 --> 01:14:57.457
<i>♪ Go and show us what we really are ♪</i>

1443
01:14:57.458 --> 01:14:59.915
[dramatic poignant music playing]

1444
01:14:59.916 --> 01:15:01.000
[gasps]

1445
01:15:02.875 --> 01:15:03.916
[gasps]

1446
01:15:05.708 --> 01:15:07.708
[breathing heavily]

1447
01:15:13.250 --> 01:15:15.540
- Oh. my God. are you okay?
- I'm so sorry.

1448
01:15:15.541 --> 01:15:16.958
- Are you all right?
- Sorry.

1449
01:15:17.791 --> 01:15:20.082
Jill! Hey. Jill! Jill. wait!

1450
01:15:20.083 --> 01:15:23.041
Why is my sister's number connected to your phone. Wes?

1451
01:15:24.166 --> 01:15:26.415
Okay. it's... It's a crazy story.

1452
01:15:26.416 --> 01:15:28.374
I… I got a work phone.

1453
01:15:28.375 --> 01:15:30.957
and then I inherited your sister's phone number.

1454
01:15:30.958 --> 01:15:33.291
- What are you talking about? How?
- After she died.

1455
01:15:34.208 --> 01:15:36.000
But my sister died in November.

1456
01:15:41.708 --> 01:15:43.791
So. you've been getting my…

1457
01:15:45.541 --> 01:15:47.583
Voicemails this entire time?

1458
01:15:48.083 --> 01:15:52.457
I was going to tell you. I just… Things kept happening.

1459
01:15:52.458 --> 01:15:53.791
- And I...
- What did you hear?

1460
01:15:56.708 --> 01:15:58.125
Wes. what did you hear?

1461
01:16:04.708 --> 01:16:05.916
My bench?

1462
01:16:06.458 --> 01:16:08.832
You knew that I was gonna be at my bench.

1463
01:16:08.833 --> 01:16:11.082
You knew about José's. about my fantasy.

1464
01:16:11.083 --> 01:16:13.375
You knew about my sister. You knew everything?

1465
01:16:13.916 --> 01:16:15.125
You knew everything.

1466
01:16:16.416 --> 01:16:19.040
- Oh. my God. I'm gonna die.
- Just… Jill.

1467
01:16:19.041 --> 01:16:20.582
- No. I knew it.
- Jill.

1468
01:16:20.583 --> 01:16:23.540
- Hold on.
- I knew that this was too good to be true.

1469
01:16:23.541 --> 01:16:25.915
- No. Jill.
- It was too perfect. I was too happy.

1470
01:16:25.916 --> 01:16:28.999
And I'm not... I'm not that lucky.

1471
01:16:29.000 --> 01:16:31.040
- I was gonna tell you.
- Take this.

1472
01:16:31.041 --> 01:16:32.791
I promise. I…

1473
01:16:33.625 --> 01:16:35.915
I know how much you loved Isabelle. and...

1474
01:16:35.916 --> 01:16:38.041
No. you do not!

1475
01:16:40.208 --> 01:16:42.500
You wouldn't know anything about that.

1476
01:16:48.583 --> 01:16:49.791
You're right.

1477
01:16:53.416 --> 01:16:54.416
I don't.

1478
01:16:55.750 --> 01:16:58.791
You deserve someone that can love you like that. and…

1479
01:17:00.166 --> 01:17:01.291
I don't know how.

1480
01:17:03.833 --> 01:17:05.291
[laughs ruefully]

1481
01:17:06.291 --> 01:17:07.625
That's crazy.

1482
01:17:09.416 --> 01:17:12.125
So you heard all my voice mails.

1483
01:17:12.875 --> 01:17:14.750
and you still don't get it.

1484
01:17:16.791 --> 01:17:21.165
Those voice mails are not a plea to the universe.

1485
01:17:21.166 --> 01:17:24.333
"God. send me somebody to love me!"

1486
01:17:28.875 --> 01:17:30.707
I don't need a man.

1487
01:17:30.708 --> 01:17:31.708
[music fades]

1488
01:17:37.000 --> 01:17:39.416
What I need is my little sister back.

1489
01:17:39.958 --> 01:17:41.958
[poignant music playing]

1490
01:17:58.375 --> 01:18:00.375
[poignant music continues]

1491
01:18:12.791 --> 01:18:13.791
[Jill] Wait.

1492
01:18:15.000 --> 01:18:16.666
No. no. no. no.

1493
01:18:18.791 --> 01:18:19.875
No. that's…

1494
01:18:22.416 --> 01:18:23.416
[exhales sharply]

1495
01:18:26.333 --> 01:18:27.458
[sobs]

1496
01:18:29.875 --> 01:18:31.500
[sobbing] Please. no!

1497
01:18:35.166 --> 01:18:37.166
[sobbing]

1498
01:18:57.250 --> 01:19:00.290
- [music fades]
- [sirens wailing distantly]

1499
01:19:00.291 --> 01:19:02.082
[Bastien] <i>Mettez-vous en rang!</i>

1500
01:19:02.083 --> 01:19:03.416
Line up!

1501
01:19:08.833 --> 01:19:09.875
Prep piggies.

1502
01:19:10.666 --> 01:19:11.915
[in unison] Yes. Chef!

1503
01:19:11.916 --> 01:19:14.707
The time has come to see which of you.

1504
01:19:14.708 --> 01:19:15.750
if any.

1505
01:19:16.583 --> 01:19:19.583
has what it takes to bake.

1506
01:19:22.500 --> 01:19:23.875
[inhales deeply]

1507
01:19:25.416 --> 01:19:26.874
Le soufflé.

1508
01:19:26.875 --> 01:19:29.624
- I just have a quick question...
- Begin!

1509
01:19:29.625 --> 01:19:31.791
[tense music playing]

1510
01:19:41.291 --> 01:19:44.166
<i>Vingt et une minutes.</i> "Twenty-one minutes."

1511
01:19:47.375 --> 01:19:48.416
[mouths] Fuck you.

1512
01:19:55.958 --> 01:19:57.333
[Bastien] <i>Quatorze minutes.</i>

1513
01:19:57.916 --> 01:19:59.166
"Fourteen minutes."

1514
01:19:59.666 --> 01:20:01.708
[tense music continues]

1515
01:20:15.500 --> 01:20:16.457
No.

1516
01:20:16.458 --> 01:20:19.457
Help me. brother. Pears. plums.
Dragon fruit with chocolate?

1517
01:20:19.458 --> 01:20:21.916
Chocolate crème? That's boring. What would you do?

1518
01:20:23.041 --> 01:20:24.707
What would you do? [Exhales]

1519
01:20:24.708 --> 01:20:28.458
[serene music playing]

1520
01:20:42.416 --> 01:20:43.458
Fruit…

1521
01:20:44.458 --> 01:20:45.583
Of the gods.

1522
01:20:48.125 --> 01:20:50.958
<i>Pistache. Pistache</i> and…

1523
01:20:52.958 --> 01:20:53.958
Raspberry coulis.

1524
01:20:57.541 --> 01:20:58.665
Oh. my God. that's perfect.

1525
01:20:58.666 --> 01:21:00.457
[both gasp]

1526
01:21:00.458 --> 01:21:01.458
[Arthur] Oh!

1527
01:21:01.916 --> 01:21:04.541
Oh. so sorry. I didn't hear you say "corner.".

1528
01:21:05.041 --> 01:21:06.540
Kumquat.

1529
01:21:06.541 --> 01:21:07.874
[laughs]

1530
01:21:07.875 --> 01:21:11.125
["Boys Wanna Be Her" by Peaches playing]

1531
01:21:11.708 --> 01:21:14.833
[laughing]

1532
01:21:16.083 --> 01:21:17.083
Okay.

1533
01:21:17.750 --> 01:21:18.750
Oh!

1534
01:21:21.791 --> 01:21:23.832
<i>♪ To you they crawl. body sprawl… ♪</i>

1535
01:21:23.833 --> 01:21:24.999
One minute.

1536
01:21:25.000 --> 01:21:27.915
<i>♪ Close call. stand tall
Doll. you make them feel so small ♪</i>

1537
01:21:27.916 --> 01:21:29.790
What in the world are you doing?

1538
01:21:29.791 --> 01:21:31.250
[laughing]

1539
01:21:31.958 --> 01:21:36.332
[Bastien] And three. two. one.

1540
01:21:36.333 --> 01:21:37.915
- Time!
- [song ends]

1541
01:21:37.916 --> 01:21:40.332
Very good. <i>Très bien.</i>

1542
01:21:40.333 --> 01:21:43.040
[suspenseful music playing]

1543
01:21:43.041 --> 01:21:45.124
<i>Le moment de vérité.</i>

1544
01:21:45.125 --> 01:21:46.375
"The moment of truth."

1545
01:21:52.541 --> 01:21:53.541
Hm.

1546
01:21:55.291 --> 01:21:58.000
It's everything you've ever taught me. Chef.

1547
01:22:00.250 --> 01:22:01.749
Enjoy.

1548
01:22:01.750 --> 01:22:04.582
- You do me great honor.
- [Arthur] Thank you. Chef.

1549
01:22:04.583 --> 01:22:06.583
[suspenseful music intensifies]

1550
01:22:08.333 --> 01:22:10.416
[inhales. exhales]

1551
01:22:12.333 --> 01:22:13.665
Yes.

1552
01:22:13.666 --> 01:22:17.290
[Jill] Soufflé pancakes with flambé kumquats.

1553
01:22:17.291 --> 01:22:21.999
cream chantilly. and ground pistachios. Chef.

1554
01:22:22.000 --> 01:22:24.000
[suspenseful music continues]

1555
01:22:46.708 --> 01:22:50.749
[Bastien] Being a baker is about precision.

1556
01:22:50.750 --> 01:22:52.249
Consistency.

1557
01:22:52.250 --> 01:22:58.665
Being a baker is not
about desperate. frantic experimentation.

1558
01:22:58.666 --> 01:23:01.750
[laughing]

1559
01:23:02.458 --> 01:23:04.707
Congratulations. young man.

1560
01:23:04.708 --> 01:23:07.374
- Me?
- [triumphant music plays]

1561
01:23:07.375 --> 01:23:09.332
- Me? What?
- [cheering]

1562
01:23:09.333 --> 01:23:10.583
[Arthur laughing]

1563
01:23:12.791 --> 01:23:14.083
Yes!

1564
01:23:15.000 --> 01:23:16.124
Yeah!

1565
01:23:16.125 --> 01:23:17.708
[laughing hysterically]

1566
01:23:20.291 --> 01:23:22.665
This is a joke. right?

1567
01:23:22.666 --> 01:23:25.624
This is a funny little ha-ha. little hee-hee joke. no?

1568
01:23:25.625 --> 01:23:27.540
- No.
- You barely tasted that.

1569
01:23:27.541 --> 01:23:31.040
And why might that be?

1570
01:23:31.041 --> 01:23:33.290
Maybe because…

1571
01:23:33.291 --> 01:23:35.166
Uh… no.

1572
01:23:35.958 --> 01:23:37.875
- It's raw?
- [cooks gasp]

1573
01:23:39.000 --> 01:23:42.082
But you knew that. didn't you?

1574
01:23:42.083 --> 01:23:46.249
Did you also know that while you're busy out there.

1575
01:23:46.250 --> 01:23:49.499
pretending to be Timothée Chalamet.

1576
01:23:49.500 --> 01:23:54.207
he's been sticking pubes in tarts and butter in freezers?

1577
01:23:54.208 --> 01:23:56.874
And you know what? Did you ever consider

1578
01:23:56.875 --> 01:24:01.833
that the girl with the dead sister might
be the one who wants to cry during sex?!

1579
01:24:02.416 --> 01:24:05.040
So. sugar tits. look at me.

1580
01:24:05.041 --> 01:24:10.165
I did not leave my home and my beautiful family

1581
01:24:10.166 --> 01:24:14.874
to waste this one wild and precious life

1582
01:24:14.875 --> 01:24:19.332
working for the goddamn Temu Gordon Ramsay.

1583
01:24:19.333 --> 01:24:20.416
You finished…

1584
01:24:23.541 --> 01:24:25.749
Fourth on <i>Top Chef</i>!

1585
01:24:25.750 --> 01:24:26.999
- It was third!
- [cooks gasp]

1586
01:24:27.000 --> 01:24:29.415
And you can drop the bad Lumière impression

1587
01:24:29.416 --> 01:24:33.999
because we all know that you're from Wisconsin.

1588
01:24:34.000 --> 01:24:35.499
And that your name…

1589
01:24:35.500 --> 01:24:36.457
No!

1590
01:24:36.458 --> 01:24:38.415
…Is Gilbert!

1591
01:24:38.416 --> 01:24:40.124
It's actually Gilbert.

1592
01:24:40.125 --> 01:24:41.790
[Jill] Who's coming with me?

1593
01:24:41.791 --> 01:24:43.666
Who's coming with me?

1594
01:24:44.875 --> 01:24:47.666
[Jill breathing heavily]

1595
01:25:03.458 --> 01:25:06.916
<i>♪ Happy birthday to me ♪</i>

1596
01:25:08.958 --> 01:25:10.958
[garage door opening]

1597
01:25:19.916 --> 01:25:21.041
[knocking on door]

1598
01:25:22.958 --> 01:25:25.124
- [Jill gasps]
- [both] Surprise!

1599
01:25:25.125 --> 01:25:26.124
Oh. my God.

1600
01:25:26.125 --> 01:25:28.582
<i>I went full Jilly Maguire.</i>

1601
01:25:28.583 --> 01:25:30.582
You told 'em to come with you. didn't you?

1602
01:25:30.583 --> 01:25:32.415
Yeah. Yeah. I did.

1603
01:25:32.416 --> 01:25:34.082
No one came with you. did they?

1604
01:25:34.083 --> 01:25:36.874
No. No. they did not.

1605
01:25:36.875 --> 01:25:38.207
[both] Cowards.

1606
01:25:38.208 --> 01:25:41.833
Not really. Where are they supposed to come to?

1607
01:25:42.416 --> 01:25:44.250
I have nothing built.

1608
01:25:44.875 --> 01:25:46.999
I have nothing to offer anyone.

1609
01:25:47.000 --> 01:25:49.332
Maybe this isn't who I am anymore.

1610
01:25:49.333 --> 01:25:52.541
And I just need to accept it. I need to grow up.

1611
01:25:53.458 --> 01:25:56.165
It's time to grow up. It's time to get a job in accounting.

1612
01:25:56.166 --> 01:25:58.540
- Honey. you're not good at math.
- So bad.

1613
01:25:58.541 --> 01:26:00.125
Maybe I'm good now.

1614
01:26:00.708 --> 01:26:03.207
I haven't counted in a long time.

1615
01:26:03.208 --> 01:26:04.500
Okay. Um…

1616
01:26:05.000 --> 01:26:08.416
We. uh. got something for you.

1617
01:26:10.291 --> 01:26:12.332
We found it in the garage.

1618
01:26:12.333 --> 01:26:14.374
[tender poignant music playing]

1619
01:26:14.375 --> 01:26:15.916
[laughs]

1620
01:26:25.583 --> 01:26:27.957
I feel like I'm letting her down.

1621
01:26:27.958 --> 01:26:29.125
Honey.

1622
01:26:30.166 --> 01:26:32.291
You are her hero.

1623
01:26:34.000 --> 01:26:36.124
Maybe her hero just wants to go back home.

1624
01:26:36.125 --> 01:26:38.708
Well. then your home will be waiting for you.

1625
01:26:39.208 --> 01:26:40.374
Always.

1626
01:26:40.375 --> 01:26:43.957
Sweetheart. there's. uh. something else in there.

1627
01:26:43.958 --> 01:26:46.000
[music fades]

1628
01:26:55.708 --> 01:26:58.915
[tender poignant music resumes]

1629
01:26:58.916 --> 01:27:00.124
What?

1630
01:27:00.125 --> 01:27:01.874
What is... What is this?

1631
01:27:01.875 --> 01:27:04.082
Izzy's college fund.

1632
01:27:04.083 --> 01:27:05.874
No. I'm not… I can't take that.

1633
01:27:05.875 --> 01:27:08.375
It's not much. but we know she'd want you to have it.

1634
01:27:10.333 --> 01:27:13.750
You could use it to come back home. get a new apartment.

1635
01:27:14.291 --> 01:27:16.083
maybe a job in accounting.

1636
01:27:16.666 --> 01:27:21.457
Or you could use it to give 'em hell.

1637
01:27:21.458 --> 01:27:22.875
What would Izzy say?

1638
01:27:26.750 --> 01:27:31.374
<i>♪ Yeah. yeah. yeah ♪</i>

1639
01:27:31.375 --> 01:27:33.333
["Show Me Love" by Robyn playing]

1640
01:27:35.583 --> 01:27:36.916
[chuckles]

1641
01:27:41.041 --> 01:27:45.665
<i>♪ Always been Told that I've got too much pride ♪</i>

1642
01:27:45.666 --> 01:27:50.457
<i>♪ Too independent to have you by my side ♪</i>

1643
01:27:50.458 --> 01:27:53.249
- [growls]
<i>- ♪ But my heart said ♪</i>

1644
01:27:53.250 --> 01:27:56.582
- No.
<i>- ♪ All of you will see ♪</i>

1645
01:27:56.583 --> 01:27:58.582
<i>♪ Just won't live for someone ♪</i>

1646
01:27:58.583 --> 01:28:00.750
<i>- ♪ Until he lives for me ♪</i>
- [cries] I suck.

1647
01:28:01.833 --> 01:28:03.457
<i>♪ Well. now I've found you ♪</i>

1648
01:28:03.458 --> 01:28:07.040
- [groans]
<i>- ♪ And I'll tell you no lie ♪</i>

1649
01:28:07.041 --> 01:28:10.040
<i>♪ This love I've got for you… ♪</i>

1650
01:28:10.041 --> 01:28:11.124
Oh. my God.

1651
01:28:11.125 --> 01:28:14.041
<i>- ♪ Now show me love ♪
- ♪ Show me love ♪</i>

1652
01:28:14.958 --> 01:28:16.791
<i>♪ Show me life ♪</i>

1653
01:28:17.541 --> 01:28:22.082
<i>♪ Baby. show me what it's all about ♪</i>

1654
01:28:22.083 --> 01:28:23.040
[yelps]

1655
01:28:23.041 --> 01:28:27.874
- [growls]
<i>- ♪ You're the one that I ever needed ♪</i>

1656
01:28:27.875 --> 01:28:32.165
<i>♪ Show me love and what it's all about ♪</i>

1657
01:28:32.166 --> 01:28:33.415
<i>♪ All right ♪</i>

1658
01:28:33.416 --> 01:28:37.707
<i>♪ Show me love. show me life ♪</i>

1659
01:28:37.708 --> 01:28:38.707
<i>♪ All right ♪</i>

1660
01:28:38.708 --> 01:28:42.874
<i>♪ Show me love and what it's all about ♪</i>

1661
01:28:42.875 --> 01:28:44.374
<i>♪ All right ♪</i>

1662
01:28:44.375 --> 01:28:46.374
[song fades]

1663
01:28:46.375 --> 01:28:49.332
- [seagulls cawing]
- [ship horn blows distantly]

1664
01:28:49.333 --> 01:28:52.083
Hi. sir. Are you interested in trying one of…

1665
01:28:52.791 --> 01:28:54.166
Hi.

1666
01:28:54.666 --> 01:28:57.790
[lilting music playing]

1667
01:28:57.791 --> 01:28:59.458
[thunder crashes]

1668
01:29:06.666 --> 01:29:08.332
- Wow.
- Hi.

1669
01:29:08.333 --> 01:29:09.333
Hey.

1670
01:29:09.750 --> 01:29:12.040
Uh. can we get the Ube All Day nachos?

1671
01:29:12.041 --> 01:29:13.207
Yes. [Laughs]

1672
01:29:13.208 --> 01:29:14.625
- [man] Thank you.
- [music fades]

1673
01:29:15.208 --> 01:29:16.915
[gasps. screams]

1674
01:29:16.916 --> 01:29:18.290
Oh. my God!

1675
01:29:18.291 --> 01:29:19.750
Shit. it's on fire!

1676
01:29:21.208 --> 01:29:22.624
[yelling]

1677
01:29:22.625 --> 01:29:23.665
[screaming]

1678
01:29:23.666 --> 01:29:26.874
[yelling and screaming continue]

1679
01:29:26.875 --> 01:29:28.374
- [extinguisher thuds]
- [man coughing]

1680
01:29:28.375 --> 01:29:29.749
[coughing]

1681
01:29:29.750 --> 01:29:30.749
[Jill] So sorry.

1682
01:29:30.750 --> 01:29:34.500
I can't make your dessert nachos…

1683
01:29:35.250 --> 01:29:36.207
Anymore.

1684
01:29:36.208 --> 01:29:37.874
I hate you.

1685
01:29:37.875 --> 01:29:39.082
I'm so sorry.

1686
01:29:39.083 --> 01:29:40.666
You've taught her to hate.

1687
01:29:43.666 --> 01:29:47.458
- [poignant music playing]
- [sobbing]

1688
01:29:55.125 --> 01:29:56.125
Stupid.

1689
01:29:56.750 --> 01:29:57.750
[knocking on door]

1690
01:29:59.000 --> 01:30:00.708
We're closed!

1691
01:30:01.791 --> 01:30:03.457
[pounding on door]

1692
01:30:03.458 --> 01:30:05.250
I said we're closed!

1693
01:30:08.750 --> 01:30:11.082
- Zella. what are you doing here?
- Shit.

1694
01:30:11.083 --> 01:30:12.125
Short circuit?

1695
01:30:12.958 --> 01:30:15.749
- I guess.
- [sighs]

1696
01:30:15.750 --> 01:30:17.499
Probably overloaded the battery.

1697
01:30:17.500 --> 01:30:19.708
Need to beef up the power system.

1698
01:30:20.625 --> 01:30:21.915
[exhales]

1699
01:30:21.916 --> 01:30:24.874
Why are you pre-making chips?
Everything needs to be served hot.

1700
01:30:24.875 --> 01:30:29.874
Well. I don't have time
to make fresh chips every single order.

1701
01:30:29.875 --> 01:30:31.374
Seems like you do.

1702
01:30:31.375 --> 01:30:33.665
Which brings me to why. in all that's holy.

1703
01:30:33.666 --> 01:30:35.207
are you parked in the Marina?

1704
01:30:35.208 --> 01:30:38.624
The Marina's pretty. and there's lots of joggers and...

1705
01:30:38.625 --> 01:30:42.291
Preppy tech bros and Karens and vegan Alo clones?

1706
01:30:42.791 --> 01:30:44.708
Everyone hates the Marina.

1707
01:30:45.208 --> 01:30:47.040
The Marina hates itself.

1708
01:30:47.041 --> 01:30:48.624
It's basically LA.

1709
01:30:48.625 --> 01:30:51.249
Let's pretend this little soft opening…

1710
01:30:51.250 --> 01:30:53.374
Extra soft. flaccid opening never happened.

1711
01:30:53.375 --> 01:30:59.332
We move the truck to our grand reopening at Hippie Hill.

1712
01:30:59.333 --> 01:31:00.582
"We"?

1713
01:31:00.583 --> 01:31:02.249
You asked who was with you. right?

1714
01:31:02.250 --> 01:31:03.290
Yeah.

1715
01:31:03.291 --> 01:31:05.165
[hopeful music playing]

1716
01:31:05.166 --> 01:31:06.833
<i>I'm</i> with you. okay?

1717
